<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="247" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="36.[136,1452,1418,1661]" box="[136,501,1418,1445]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,1418,1444]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<collectingCountry box="[321,389,1418,1444]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[442,497,1419,1445]" name="Peru" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[136,1452,1418,1661]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1454,1480]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Notes:—</emphasis>
This species had been previously known only from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1039,1110,1454,1480]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, but this species was recently documented from Tingo María National Park, 
<collectingCountry box="[657,708,1491,1517]" name="Peru" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">Peru</collectingCountry>
(Ocupa 
<emphasis box="[804,861,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">et al.</emphasis>
2017). Unfortunately, no herbarium specimens were prepared. The habit and flower of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[533,689,1526,1552]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulvinatus">
<emphasis box="[533,689,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. pulvinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich. &amp; Galeotti" box="[844,994,1527,1552]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">
<emphasis box="[844,994,1527,1552]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">M. congestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but mainly distinguished by its column apex frequently bidentate on both sides and generally apiculate lip 
<emphasis box="[913,936,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">vs</emphasis>
. with an acute tooth on both sides and apex acute to obtuse. Since the illustration cited by Barbosa Rodrigues in the original publication of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." box="[1193,1330,1598,1625]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="36" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulvinata">
<emphasis box="[1193,1330,1598,1625]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">A. pulvinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only remaining original material associated with this species, it is designated here as 
<typeStatus box="[1031,1137,1634,1660]" pageId="36" pageNumber="247">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
